J4mpRSISRDs6UA==\",\"summary\":[{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Exploring reflections in testing**\\n\\nI’m considering how potential test helpers work, especially with the Base TestSerializable abstract class and its interaction with reflection configuration. I’m trying to understand what happens when the ReflectionSerializer attempts to walk through super, particularly if the class isn’t included in the reflection config. I wonder if I'm missing key details about how reflection processes these scenarios or if it just skips over them entirely. It's a bit puzzling!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Clarifying constructor access**\\n\\nI’m considering a public static class with no constructor. If the class is public, the implicit default constructor is public too. I realized the default constructor shares the same access level as the class. I might need to set the `SerializableChild` via `collectionType.getConstructor().newInstance()`, ensuring that the constructor is public. I also need to reflect the config changes with `$` names, but I worry if the dynamic coverage report will view this manual metadata as \\\"dynamic access.\\\" I'll need to write that file.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_FsNww9T47pjHLkQPVTip3Hcu|fc_0257d767d56de5ab0169f633c405a0819cae5b49a3eaf26d1e", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/org.liquibase/liquibase-core/5.0.1/src/test/java/org_liquibase/liquibase_core/AbstractLiquibaseSerializableTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage org_liquibase.liquibase_core;\n\nimport liquibase.parser.core.ParsedNode;\nimport liquibase.resource.ClassLoaderResourceAccessor;\nimport liquibase.serializer.AbstractLiquibaseSerializable;\nimport liquibase.serializer.LiquibaseSerializable.SerializationType;\nimport liquibase.util.ISODateFormat;\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\n\nimport java.util.ArrayList;\nimport java.util.Date;\nimport java.util.List;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class AbstractLiquibaseSerializableTest {\n\n    @Test\n    void loadsExplicitCollectionAndNestedSerializableFields() throws Exception {\n        ParentSerializable serializable = new ParentSerializable();\n        ParsedNode parsedNode = new ParsedNode(null, \"parent\");\n        parsedNode.addChild(new ParsedNode(null, \"children\")\n                .addChild(new ParsedNode(null, \"child\")\n                        .addChild(null, \"value\", \"collection-value\")));\n        parsedNode.addChild(new ParsedNode(null, \"child\")\n                .addChild(null, \"value\", \"nested-value\"));\n\n        serializable.load(parsedNode, new ClassLoaderResourceAccessor());\n\n        assertThat(serializable.getChildren())\n                .extracting(SerializableChild::getValue)\n                .containsExactly(\"collection-value\");\n        assertThat(serializable.getChild().getValue()).isEqualTo(\"nested-value\");\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void loadsCollectionWhenParsedNodeUsesElementName() throws Exception {\n        ImplicitCollectionSerializable serializable = new ImplicitCollectionSerializable();\n        ParsedNode parsedNode = new ParsedNode(null, \"parent\");\n        parsedNode.addChild(new ParsedNode(null, \"child\")\n                .addChild(null, \"value\", \"implicit-collection-value\"));\n\n        serializable.load(parsedNode, new ClassLoaderResourceAccessor());\n\n        assertThat(serializable.getChildren())\n                .extracting(SerializableChild::getValue)\n                .containsExactly(\"implicit-collection-value\");\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void loadsEscapedValuesRequiringConstructors() throws Exception {\n        EscapedValuesSerializable serializable = new EscapedValuesSerializable();\n        ParsedNode parsedNode = new ParsedNode(null, \"escapedValues\");\n        parsedNode.addChild(null, \"timestamp\", \"2024-01-02T03:04:05!{java.util.Date}\");\n        parsedNode.addChild(null, \"builder\", \"liquibase!{java.lang.StringBuilder}\");\n\n        serializable.load(parsedNode, new ClassLoaderResourceAccessor());\n\n        assertThat(new ISODateFormat().format(serializable.getTimestamp())).isEqualTo(\"2024-01-02T03:04:05\");\n        assertThat(serializable.getBuilder().toString()).isEqualTo(\"liquibase\");\n    }\n\n    public abstract static class TestSerializable extends AbstractLiquibaseSerializable {\n        @Override\n        public String getSerializedObjectNamespace() {\n            return null;\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static class ParentSerializable extends TestSerializable {\n        private final List<SerializableChild> children = new ArrayList<>();\n        private SerializableChild child;\n\n        @Override\n        public String getSerializedObjectName() {\n            return \"parent\";\n        }\n\n        public List<SerializableChild> getChildren() {\n            return children;\n        }\n\n        public SerializableChild getChild() {\n            return child;\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static class ImplicitCollectionSerializable extends TestSerializable {\n        private final List<SerializableChild> children = new ArrayList<>();\n\n        @Override\n        public String getSerializedObjectName() {\n            return \"parent\";\n        }\n\n        public List<SerializableChild> getChildren() {\n            return children;\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static class SerializableChild extends TestSerializable {\n        private String value;\n\n        @Override\n        public String getSerializedObjectName() {\n            return \"child\";\n        }\n\n        public String getValue() {\n            return value;\n        }\n\n        public void setValue(String value) {\n            this.value = value;\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static class EscapedValuesSerializable extends TestSerializable {\n        private Date timestamp;\n        private StringBuilder builder;\n\n        @Override\n        public String getSerializedObjectName() {\n            return \"escapedValues\";\n        }\n\n        @Override\n        public SerializationType getSerializableFieldType(String field) {\n            return SerializationType.NAMED_FIELD;\n        }\n\n        public Date getTimestamp() {\n            return timestamp;\n        }\n\n        public void setTimestamp(Date timestamp) {\n            this.timestamp = timestamp;\n        }\n\n        public StringBuilder getBuilder() {\n            return builder;\n        }\n\n        public void setBuilder(StringBuilder builder) {\n            this.builder = builder;\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 419, "output": 2047, "cacheRead": 27136, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 29602, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777742774245, "responseId": "resp_0257d767d56de5ab0169f633b6b494819c96036f7722986bd4"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_FsNww9T47pjHLkQPVTip3Hcu|fc_0257d767d56de5ab0169f633c405a0819cae5b49a3eaf26d1e", "toolName": "write", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Successfully wrote 5092 bytes to tests/src/org.liquibase/liquibase-core/5.0.1/src/test/java/org_liquibase/liquibase_core/AbstractLiquibaseSerializableTest.java"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777742793207}]}
