eep fields package-private since they’re directly instantiated by the test? There's the active class calling `getSerializableFields`, and the `ReflectionSerializer` can set accessible fields on package-private classes without issues.\n\nHowever, I wonder if it's safer to have them public. It seems that native configurations with `$` are unavoidable for nested public classes. I might need to use the `access-filter` with exact class patterns like \"java.util.Date\" to potentially match inner classes as well.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0257d767d56de5ab0169f63478c410819c970404da94e49c0d\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp9jSIYyUVLWD702lLAFOrBXuY9ZwJZm2uawtXgEsbGMcSMI-pQOXtFnzMNPPvWXvainQR4Fsn8h9Kqqw28haJEwc6ldprpfvcBe1N5YiSPeEymJl16zHH2Y69Fd7mCjnbIrDsKNMpr8fFc5IScXRs_82tvfnWiLOdbtO7LONbPo6v9UZa9ZK_W_i2pS8ExPCvNB47p0irRX3U9hZszjPKLG_iJQ1g3uvfvmHlX_kyu79mR_kqZbk5cAmbFBse3hb0ECj__gUpAAK8m9DUAjDX80fq52-C0-U7XCKui2FxQTTF4jrzzM3eJY85Xvi1TnIHfTZ3D37AzUHBwCcDjh_AbFatdMp-SopY0_DgV01uqHow3TajloKkAW9gvrnhY_Am2S-_tokglzAhvw9Yh5Rzvhl44Gm2UOq_RERrVdKu7H5v12BGgj7B5CzdPZkWCpWsztq4AIXiLRVgblK0RAtp1ulYOWFwiynCn0iLFG-CtN3yihZNmMnyUdfqXjI2jLWhQRhxwWDuL_S1xfzhoAev11R-yFSU1mUXznhI9I5sfisbUbVlHbZLUaA-j2zakTkOAZSfSzDC7AlnOZbeDzoqDMpnfTDxGgSFcSnvZXeNsQfUxlUQwjjxTUl6Rhg9LLQrJvNDxgLvwYBW_j2dJItTgqpVjyuuBPjvUQlyEwdX9XcgbVtqGZO8oxzNdB1fOUT013K85z-EHvUYyqHK-FHiVqlbg9azWFWH6IxMngwp0gqCHd_aUFm6VkGjuMtLdwmn4bEGxYmrOaONJhKqv5AHGHgrIAVKsjP9FX7hd9ieXOxMkQdA60-P6dj0oVELdgxeggMIbd0FXbY68pXYvvgXD8e3HKTADabNkKOYGeJyrrMCrHaNo9WfZjzV16m7LHc78TFdBVmDyy3ZU1GjioqQxjyEIfDsc3bIs2DkjrX5A1MuvWlEiyPcIL5KoZtXXM_LBomkduTL02crAf_bvhw--0DECJoktPxsJ8ETsNusiGTKfDdeeZG-SRn-e3MReEZ6-r9582QREvT057ZJu20W577_5vuKl_TVfAnYSh_un8OJjn_DeiDazSrQeHjCW0tcGOHUfcI-nyJ6rwdeaxbu3YFtAufF45fm28_P9RzX2TqB9myKs3BbCwZcItsY_-QR5IBv5lVXZcc1hGDdI20G9Q4Rtij8K2c7OFkqC1wlJErQ9Iyyuh8cz3lcUJRykuuwgzPt0KP7T0ONEdI0EoOOXrcLDm-M3eYHNb9sUJ8kGbYjj7LlIuJhcI5LFdXRxm7kUPHTkoRqg1P98pbntuNOfQCOastWBumF3QgQ6AGnTBgVti9adHi8jfyRezZ2DtN